  "guide": {
    "title": "CDSS User Guide",
    "step1_title": "Select Evaluation Module",
    "step1_desc": "On the main page (Clinical Calculator), choose one of the three available tabs according to the patient's clinical needs: <b>AI Mortality Prediction</b>, <b>AI Length of Stay Prediction</b>, or <b>Clinical Dosage Recommendation</b>.",
    "step2_title": "Input Clinical Parameters",
    "step2_desc": "Enter the patient's clinical data obtained from medical records or recent laboratory tests. You can use the <b>Auto-calculate</b> feature for CTP and GFR (CKD-EPI 2021) scores if the constituent parameters are available, or input them manually.",
    "step3_title": "Select Medications (Dosage Module Only)",
    "step3_desc": "If using the Dosage Recommendation module, check the medications planned for evaluation, then indicate if there are accompanying acute complications (such as AKI, Sepsis, or Hepatorenal Syndrome).",
    "step4_title": "Analysis & Professional Verification",
    "step4_desc": "Click the process button to send data to the artificial intelligence server. <b>Important:</b> The results displayed by the system (both probability and dosage ranges) serve as clinical decision support. Perform final verification based on your professional medical judgment."
  },
